<h2>Miscellaneous Debuggery Notes:</h2>
<li>With i.c { fill(); }, those brackets are compulsory.//
<li>In the supposed //~#bug of broken i.c{ li } selecting, the i.c{ id= } bit was simply not input properly in inline [html].//
<li>With [rgb] colors, to get brighter, ie. in the case of "violet", max out red to the hundreds on. Then add shades of blue. Stronger than the reds value of course.//
<li class="nn"> i.c { rgba(113,0,225,1) } [rgb] is a good "violet" that looks a bit like "beautyberry"; <a href="http://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Callicarpa">here</a>.//
<li>The i.c { h2 } i.c{nth-of-type} [css] selector used before works only "within parent" and not "across entire document" as is needed. Thus the whole line of <xmp> 	/** h2:nth-of-type(2) {color: rgb(3,3,120,1);} /*navy?*/ **/ </xmp> is to be #excluded entirely from styles.//
<li> The i.c{ :before } pseudo-selector(?) in the i.c{ li } elements does not include the "bullet-character" itself. Thus line <xmp> li:before {content: '||'; margin-left:-23%} </xmp> in #css has been #excluded.//
<li>Line <xmp> #dn li::first-letter {color:rgba(3,3,120,1); font-family:courier; font-weight:bolder;} /*^navy*/ </xmp> has been #excluded because #css selector i.c { ::first-letter } includes this selection and is therefore rendered obselte in required purpose.//
<li> 	<h3>150814...</h3>
